FT  22 OCT 92 / World News in Brief: Train caught in bomb blast
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A passing train was hit by flying debris when a bomb exploded on a railway
track at Edmonton, north London. Three passengers were slightly hurt. The
IRA claimed that an advance warning was ignored, but British Rail denied
receiving one.
